**Describe the bug**

Editing an item and triggering it's removal from the data grid items list results in an NRE when committing the edit.

**To Reproduce**

Steps to reproduce the behavior:

1. Start from the Avalonia MVVM template, and install data grid
2. On `MainWindow.xaml`:

    ```xaml
    <DataGrid AutoGenerateColumns="True" Items="{Binding Items}" />
    ```
3. On `MainWindowViewModel.cs`:

    ```cs
    public class MainWindowViewModel : ViewModelBase
    {
        public sealed class Item : ViewModelBase
        {
            private string _value;

            public Item(MainWindowViewModel owner, string value)
            {
                _value = value;

                this.WhenAnyValue(x => x.Value).Subscribe(_ => owner.Items.Remove(this));
            }

            public string Value
            {
                get => _value;
                set => this.RaiseAndSetIfChanged(ref _value, value);
            }
        }

        public MainWindowViewModel()
        {
            Items.Add(new Item(this, "A"));
            Items.Add(new Item(this, "B"));
        }

        public ObservableCollection<Item> Items { get; } = new ObservableCollection<Item>();
    }
    ```
4. Run the app, and edit one of the values, then commit the edit, and it throws an NRE.

**Expected behavior**

The item should be successfully removed from the list.

**Desktop (please complete the following information):**

- OS: Windows 11
- Version: 11.0.0-preview2

