We don't currently have `EventSetter`. The solution for now would be to handle `Gestures.DoubleTapped` in the `TreeView` and then look up the `TreeViewItem` from `e.Sender` in the handler. Unfortunately it looks like attached events are currently broken too so this will have to be done in code:

```csharp
    public class MainWindow : Window
    {
        public MainWindow()
        {
            InitializeComponent();
            var treeView = this.FindControl<TreeView>("treeView");
            treeView.AddHandler(Gestures.DoubleTappedEvent, TreeView_DoubleTapped);
        }

        public void TreeView_DoubleTapped(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)
        {
            var item = ((IVisual)e.Source).GetSelfAndVisualAncestors()
                .OfType<TreeViewItem>()
                .FirstOrDefault();

            if (item != null)
            {
                // Do whatever you need with item here.
                e.Handled = true;
            }
        }
    }
```

